Overview

Demonstrates Lender Operating System behavior when a borrower fails underwriting validation requirements during processing.

The recording validates borrower qualification controls, governance enforcement, routing decisions, audit logging, and operational visibility when a loan application cannot proceed through the standard approval workflow.

Recording Objectives

Demonstrate:

Borrower intake

Loan type tagging

Borrower enters Process OS

Validation failure occurs

Routing decision executed

Governance updates

Audit logging

Final failed disposition
Recording Scenario

Example:

Borrower Application

Credit Score:
580

Required Threshold:
620

Expected Outcome:

Validation Fail

Routing Failure

Governance Updates

No Approval Processing
